Only the part of the file chemical-disease association (with directEvidence: therapeutic or marker/mechanism) is integrated into neo4j and only a part of exposure-event association (only with positive correltaion with outcome).

I use the file from June 2017.
The files can be down loaded by http://ctdbase.org/downloads/.

Davis AP, Grondin CJ, Johnson RJ, Sciaky D, King BL, McMorran R, Wiegers J, Wiegers TC, Mattingly CJ. The Comparative Toxicogenomics Database: update 2017. Nucleic Acids Res. 2016 Sep 19;[Epub ahead of print] 
